Basic.desc: Basic test vectors use the simplest possible inputs. These inputs often overlap with inputs from standards and RFCs. One goal of such test vectors is to simply detect distinct algorithms.

CounterOverflow.desc: The counter for the CTR mode in EAX is reduced modulo 2**128. Other encryption mode reduce the CTR modulo 2**32.The test vector has been constrcuted to check for correct reduction of the counter.

ModifiedTag.desc: The tag of this test vector has been modified. Decryption should fail.

Pseudorandom.desc: The test vector has been generated pseudorandomly.

SpecialCaseCt.desc: The test vector has been constructed, so that the ciphertext is a special case.

SpecialCaseKey.desc: The test vector uses a special case key
